# Fluff Date: 2026-02-19 20:53:42
overview:<p>The Surtur was introduced in 3139 as the first BattleMech fully designed and built within the borders of the Hanseatic League. Produced by the Lüneburg Vehicle Corporation on Braunschweig, the fifty-five ton medium 'Mech represented a milestone for the Deep Periphery trading nation, whose industrial base had only recently achieved technology levels comparable to the pre-Jihad Inner Sphere. Commissioned by the governing Council of Merchants as a symbol of Hanseatic self-sufficiency, the Surtur was designed from the outset as a skirmisher and close-quarters melee fighter. Its aggressive, fire-oriented combat philosophy set it apart from the older Star League-era designs that had previously formed the backbone of the Hanseatic Defense Force.</p>

capabilities:<p>Built for speed and brutality at close range, the Surtur mounts a 330-rated extra-light fusion engine that pushes the chassis to a respectable ninety kilometers per hour. A supercharger provides temporary bursts up to one hundred and twenty kilometers per hour, allowing the 'Mech to close rapidly with its targets. Twelve tons of standard armor plate over an endo-steel frame give the design considerable staying power for a medium 'Mech, ensuring it can weather incoming fire during its approach.</p><p>The Surtur's armament reflects its intended role as a close-combat brawler. Seven flamers, three mounted in each side torso and one in the left arm, generate punishing heat against enemy 'Mechs while also proving effective against infantry and conventional forces. A pair of SRM-6 launchers deliver devastating short-range missile salvos, and a sword mounted in the right arm allows the Surtur to deliver crippling melee strikes to overheated or vulnerable opponents. However, the single ton of SRM ammunition feeds from the center torso without CASE protection, a significant design flaw that leaves the 'Mech vulnerable to catastrophic ammunition explosions. Twelve double heat sinks struggle to manage the thermal load when all weapons fire simultaneously, requiring disciplined heat management from its pilots.</p>

deployment:<p>No factory variants of the Surtur are known to have been produced. The design's brief production run under the Hanseatic League, followed by the disruption of the Hanseatic Crusade and the subsequent reorganization of Braunschweig's manufacturing under the Scorpion Empire, left little opportunity for the development of formal variant configurations.</p>

history:<p>The Surtur's origins are tied directly to the industrial ambitions of the Hanseatic League. In 2937, a fully intact Star League Defense Force BattleMech repair facility was discovered near the city of Lüneburg on Braunschweig. For decades this automated facility served as a critical maintenance asset for the League's aging military equipment. By the turn of the thirty-second century, growing concern over the neighboring Escorpión Imperio prompted the Council of Merchants to authorize construction of the Lüneburg Vehicle Corporation adjacent to the old SLDF site. When production difficulties arose, components were quietly shipped to the SLDF facility where its automated machinery completed final assembly.</p><p>The success of the Lüneburg factory enabled the League to produce heavier 'Mech designs such as the Thunderbolt, Awesome, and Zeus, and spurred the establishment of additional manufacturing on other Hanseatic worlds. By the 3120s, the League's industrial capacity had reached pre-Jihad technological levels, and the Council of Merchants commissioned the development of an indigenous BattleMech design. The resulting Surtur entered production in 3139, representing a point of national pride as the first 'Mech conceived entirely within Hanseatic borders. The importance of the Lüneburg facility led to the permanent posting of Regional Defense Force Six to Braunschweig, and Surturs quickly came to form a substantial portion of that garrison's strength.</p><p>The Surtur's operational life under the Hanseatic banner proved tragically short. In January 3140, the Escorpión Imperio launched the Hanseatic Crusade, an all-out invasion aimed at conquering the League. Clan Goliath Scorpion's warriors brought overwhelming force against the scattered Hanseatic garrisons, and one of the Scorpion objectives was the capture of the new 'Mech type and its production facilities on Braunschweig. By October 3140, the League's capital of Bremen had fallen, and the Council of Merchants destroyed themselves rather than surrender. By early 3141, all Hanseatic worlds had been secured and the Scorpion Empire was proclaimed.</p><p>Following the conquest, the Lüneburg Vehicle Corporation was retooled, rebranded, and consolidated with other former Hanseatic manufacturing operations under the new Imperial BattleMechs banner. The fate of the Surtur design under Scorpion Empire management remains unclear, as Clan Goliath Scorpion possesses access to far more advanced Clan technology. Whether the design continues in any capacity within the Empire's expanded industrial base, or has been supplanted entirely by Clan designs, is not widely known outside the Deep Periphery.</p>

